<TITLE> Khaleda's nephew Tuhin gets 8 years for tax evasion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Monday sentenced Shahrin Islam Tuhin, nephew of former prime minister Khaleda Zia, to 8 years rigorous imprisonment for evading income tax. The special court of judge Tanzina Ismailset up on the Jatiya Sangsad premisesalso fined Tuhin to Tk 92 lakh, or a further 9 months in prison on failure to pay the fine. The National Board of Revenue filed the case on Nov 25 against Tuhin, who is currently fugitive in the case. The accused was alleged of providing false information in his income tax returns for the tax years 1998-99 to 2006-07, and evading tax of Tk 81,81,082. The charge-sheet for this case was prepared on Dec 17. Forty people gave evidence in the case. Shahrin Islam Tuhin was elected as BNP MP for Nilfamari-1 constituency on Feb 15, 1996. bdnews24.
